From: gmonsoon <greataji13@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 21:45:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] power: supply: qcom_pm8150b_charger: detect online via power
 path status

The current online detection reads USBIN_INT_RT_STS (0x310 from the
charger base) and checks USBIN_PLUGIN_RT_STS_BIT. On PM8150B this can
fail to reflect an attached VBUS source, so UPower reports "on-battery"
and phosh never shows a charging indicator even though the battery is
charging.

Use POWER_PATH_STATUS (0x10B from base) instead, matching the Google
SM8150 BMS driver: online is true when USE_USBIN_BIT or USE_DCIN_BIT is
set together with VALID_INPUT_POWER_SOURCE_STS_BIT.

This only changes the userspace-visible POWER_SUPPLY_PROP_ONLINE report;
hardware charging control is unaffected.

--- a/drivers/power/supply/qcom_pm8150b_charger.c
+++ b/drivers/power/supply/qcom_pm8150b_charger.c
@@ -324,14 +324,15 @@ static int smb5_get_prop_usb_online(struct smb5_chip *chip, int *val)
 {
 	unsigned int stat;
 	int rc;

-	rc = regmap_read(chip->regmap, chip->base + USBIN_INT_RT_STS_OFFSET, &stat);
+	rc = regmap_read(chip->regmap, chip->base + POWER_PATH_STATUS, &stat);
 	if (rc < 0) {
-		dev_err(chip->dev, "Couldn't read USBIN_RT_STS rc=%d\n", rc);
+		dev_err(chip->dev, "Couldn't read POWER_PATH_STATUS rc=%d\n", rc);
 		return rc;
 	}

-	*val = (stat & USBIN_PLUGIN_RT_STS_BIT) ? 1 : 0;
+	*val = !!(stat & (P_PATH_USE_USBIN_BIT | P_PATH_USE_DCIN_BIT)) &&
+	       !!(stat & P_PATH_VALID_INPUT_POWER_SOURCE_STS_BIT);
 	return 0;
 }

